\title{ProseMirror}

\p{[ProseMirror](https://prosemirror.net/) is a modular library of components
  for building rich content editors, written in TypeScript. It is often used
  with [TipTap](https://tiptap.dev/)
  ([HN](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=36957204)), which builds on
  ProseMirror to make it easier for standard use cases.}

\subtree{
\title{Collaborative editing}

\p{ProseMirror supports real-time collaborative editing through several
different backends:
\ul{
  \li{[prosemirror-collab](https://prosemirror.net/docs/guide/#collab):
  ProseMirror's built-in module based on a central authority, \em{not} Yjs}
  \li{[prosemirror-collab-commit](https://github.com/stepwisehq/prosemirror-collab-commit):
  third-party module for commit-based collaborative editing}
  \li{[Hocuspocus](https://tiptap.dev/docs/hocuspocus/introduction):
  integrates Yjs with ProseMirror/TipTap}
}}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example applications}

\p{Open-source rich-text editors built using
TypeScript, ProseMirror/TipTap, and in some cases Yjs:
\ul{
  \li{[Vrite](https://vrite.io/)
  ([demo](https://editor.vrite.io/),
   [GitHub](https://github.com/vriteio/vrite)
   [HN](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=36446045)):
  WYSIWYG Markdown editor}
  \li{[BlockNote](https://www.blocknotejs.org/)
  ([GitHub](https://github.com/TypeCellOS/BlockNote),
   [HN](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=32764493)):
  block-based editor inspired by Notion}
  \li{[Novel](https://novel.sh/)
  ([GitHub](https://github.com/steven-tey/novel),
   [HN](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=36360789)):
  another Notion-style editor}
}}
}
